  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A Safe Learning Space for Zimbabwean ECD Learners</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide ablutions for the Early Childhood Development (ECD) classes in Zimbabwe&apos;s Hwange National Park to improve hygiene &amp; sanitation &amp; reduce their chances of contracting dangerous diseases like typhoid &amp; cholera, which are prevalent in the area. This project will also build a fence around the perimeter to keep the children safe from dangerous wild animals which occur here in high numbers. The ultimate goal is to increase ECD admissions &amp; give children a better start in life.</narrative>
  </description>
